Title: Ethics Plan for Energy Data Projects
1. Principles

This ethics plan is based on two core principles: fairness and privacy.
Fairness ensures that data-driven decisions do not discriminate against any group or region. In energy projects, this means avoiding biased predictions that may disadvantage certain communities in access to energy resources or infrastructure planning.
Privacy focuses on protecting sensitive data, including consumption patterns and user behavior. Data should be anonymized and securely stored to prevent misuse.

2. Bias in Energy Data (Detection & Mitigation)

Bias in energy datasets can arise from incomplete data, regional imbalance, or historical inequalities.

Detection: Use statistical checks to identify skewed distributions (e.g., overrepresentation of urban areas vs rural).

Mitigation: Apply techniques such as data balancing, normalization, and fairness-aware algorithms. Regular audits should be conducted to ensure models remain unbiased over time.

3. Case Example: Bias in Timeline Prediction Model

In energy project management, timeline prediction models may show bias if trained on limited or skewed datasets.
For example, if historical data mostly includes fast-completed urban projects, the model may underestimate timelines for rural or complex regions.
To address this:

Include diverse datasets

Validate across multiple scenarios

Monitor prediction errors across different project types

4. Regulations and Compliance

This plan aligns with global data protection standards such as GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation).
Key compliance steps include:

Collecting data with consent

Ensuring transparency in data usage

Allowing users to access or delete their data

Maintaining secure storage and processing systems

5. Application: Fair Timeline Prediction

The ethical approach will be applied to fair timeline prediction in energy projects.
This ensures:

Equal consideration for all project types

Transparent model decisions

Reliable and unbiased planning outputs

This plan supports responsible AI usage and promotes trust in energy data systems.